A Man enters a darkened room.  He flagellates.  This goes on for hours.  His roommate enters the darkened room. 
	Roommate: What are you flagellating in here?
The man takes pause.
	Roommate: -silence-
The man grows a beard.
	Roommate: Nice beard.
 	Man: Get out.
The roommate lights a few cigarettes.  Upstairs, the sounds of a woman bathing echo throughout the buildings dilapidated ventilation system.  A knock comes at the door.  The man and his roommate look at each other, and take pause to reflect inwardly.  The knock repeats.  The roommate releases a heaving sigh.  He turns to answer the knock.  The man raises his hand with a protective air maternal tenderness.
	Man: Wait-
The roommate stops.  Turns.
	Man: Take my beard.  For good luck.
-beat-
	Roommate: All of it?
The Man nods, gravely.  The Roommate returns the nod, and acquires the beard.  He takes three steps to exit the room, and four more to the door, revealing the silhouetted face of a Jamaican.
	Jamaican: Can I borrow ah cup ah sugar, mon?
Flagellation has resumed in the darkened room.  What can only be described as a violent flapping emanates from the darkness.
	Jamaican: (pause) Ees et ah bahd time, mon?
-beat-
	Jamaican: Nice beard.
	Roommate: Get out.
	Jamaican: Gone.
:::POOF!:::
The roommate lingers in a cloud of Jamaican residue for only a moment before returning to the darkened room and light another cigarette.  The Man breathes.  They stand.  This goes on for hours.

It is turned into a 3-part mini-series.  What is this world coming to?

was a little sick. thursday.  sick on friday.  real sick on saturday.  went to hospital.  they thought i had menengitis.  they did a spinal tap.  im feeling better, but now my back is in excrucating pain.  shit.

i just did my final performance with my improv class.  i feel it went very well, and it was a whole lot of fun.  thanks to everyone who came to support me, i hope you all had fun.  and for all those who don't know, ive decided to shift my focus from music, education and buisness to comedy.  then later when ty and i are independantly rich and connected, we can start our school.  rock on.

Saw Blues Explosion last night.  Rocked my fucking sock off.  if anyone ever gets a chance to see them, go.  its everything i think a rock show should be.  they must have played 45 songs, all high energy and all incredible.  but bring ear plugs, because i blew my ears out, and they are still ringging and hurting a little bit a day later.  fucking rock and roll, man.  i love it.
